content:
An official from China’s central bank also recently <a href="https://www.theblockcrypto.com/linked/62418/chinas-central-bank-says-digital-currency-could-be-used-in-2022-winter-olympics" data-v-f87c67ca="">confirmed</a> that some state-owned banks are conducting internal tests of digital currency in four cities - Shenzhen, Suzhou, Xiong'an New Area and Chengdu. <br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
The official further said that the digital currency could also be used in the 2022 Winter Olympics event, hinting at a possible launch by mid-2021.&nbsp;
